WEBVTT

00:00.768 --> 00:03.771
[tone]

00:03.804 --> 00:09.677
[music playing]

00:09.710 --> 00:11.245
Rose, where's that itch cream?

00:11.279 --> 00:14.115
I've got me one fierce bug bite.

00:14.148 --> 00:17.285
Dan, you know that
mirror in the bathroom?

00:17.318 --> 00:20.154
Well, that mirror is
actually a magical door that

00:20.188 --> 00:24.258
opens into a world of medicine.

00:24.292 --> 00:26.527
I looked in the medicine
cabinet, It ain't in there?

00:26.560 --> 00:29.063
Are you sure it was the
medicine cabinet you looked in?

00:29.097 --> 00:30.098
Was it cold?

00:30.131 --> 00:33.234
Was there milk
and beer in there?

00:33.267 --> 00:34.135
Come on.

00:34.168 --> 00:35.903
I can't sleep with the light on.

00:35.936 --> 00:38.439
Well, I can't read
with the light off.

00:38.472 --> 00:40.108
I looked in every shelf.

00:40.141 --> 00:42.176
I even moved a jar.

00:42.210 --> 00:43.277
[shushing]

00:43.311 --> 00:44.745
Come on, if I
don't get some sleep,

00:44.778 --> 00:46.514
I'm going to be in a
bad mood all day long.

00:46.547 --> 00:48.649
Do how is that different
from any other day of the week?

00:48.682 --> 00:49.550
Ha, ha.

00:49.583 --> 00:51.785
Good one, Becky.

00:51.819 --> 00:52.853
I'm tired and I want to sleep.

00:52.886 --> 00:54.288
Turn off the damn light.

00:54.322 --> 00:56.724
I'm not tired, and
I don't want to sleep.

00:56.757 --> 00:58.292
Woah, woah,
where's that cream?

00:58.326 --> 01:00.961
I got me another bite.

01:00.994 --> 01:02.330
You can go
downstairs and read.

01:02.363 --> 01:05.966
You can turn on every
light the damn house then.

01:05.999 --> 01:07.168
I go downstairs and--

01:07.201 --> 01:09.203
They fight for three
days over a light?

01:09.237 --> 01:12.273
No, Dan, they are not
actually fighting about a light.

01:12.306 --> 01:14.575
The light is just an excuse for
what they're really fighting

01:14.608 --> 01:16.244
about, like that
time we had the fight

01:16.277 --> 01:18.846
about you and your bad breath.

01:18.879 --> 01:20.114
What do you mean?

01:20.148 --> 01:23.217
I was actually mad because
you came home late, so you

01:23.251 --> 01:24.185
brushed your teeth for nothing.

01:26.287 --> 01:36.330
[music playing]

01:36.330 --> 01:46.340
[music playing]

02:08.362 --> 02:10.298
[laughter]

02:10.331 --> 02:14.735
[music playing]

02:14.768 --> 02:17.638
Well, Roseanne,
reviews are in.

02:17.671 --> 02:20.107
Our suggestion box is full.

02:20.140 --> 02:21.342
You know what that means?

02:21.375 --> 02:25.879
Yeah, time to get a new
box with no slot on the top.

02:25.913 --> 02:30.117
You know, I wonder how someone
with your obvious people skills

02:30.150 --> 02:32.820
could be afraid of a
little suggestion box.

02:32.853 --> 02:34.222
Well, it's demeaning.

02:34.255 --> 02:38.892
It reminds our regular customers
that they're unable to write.

02:38.926 --> 02:41.495
Well, just remember
there is nothing to fear,

02:41.529 --> 02:46.434
but well everything
that's inside.

02:46.467 --> 02:49.403
Suggestion number one,
the meat is a little dry.

02:49.437 --> 02:51.239
I would agree with that.

02:51.272 --> 02:53.674
Suggestion number 2,
make that up tight

02:53.707 --> 02:57.077
blond guy stop hovering over
us while we're trying to--

02:57.110 --> 02:57.911
eat.

03:01.849 --> 03:04.117
I would agree with that.

03:04.151 --> 03:08.989
Now let's see,
suggestion number three.

03:09.022 --> 03:10.157
Lose the waiter guy.

03:10.190 --> 03:11.459
He reminds me of my mother.

03:15.396 --> 03:17.631
Well, aren't we
clever, Roseanne,

03:17.665 --> 03:19.667
stuffing the suggestion box?

03:19.700 --> 03:21.435
This is your
suggestion, isn't it?

03:21.469 --> 03:22.270
Guess again.

03:28.942 --> 03:32.746
Well, luckily, I don't
value the opinion of anyone

03:32.780 --> 03:36.450
who would choose to eat here.

03:36.484 --> 03:37.451
Sorry I'm late.

03:37.485 --> 03:38.819
The baby kept me up all night.

03:38.852 --> 03:40.888
Well, you married him.

03:40.921 --> 03:42.290
I was up all night, too.

03:42.323 --> 03:43.291
Why?

03:43.324 --> 03:44.492
Because Becky and
Mark were having

03:44.525 --> 03:45.859
a big fight in the next room.

03:45.893 --> 03:50.264
And it's hard to sleep when
you're wearing a stethoscope.

03:50.298 --> 03:51.899
They certainly have been
fighting a lot lately.

03:51.932 --> 03:53.233
Hm.

03:53.267 --> 03:54.702
I try to get Becky to the
talk about it, but she won't.

03:54.735 --> 03:56.036
Oh, it's such a
shame when a daughter

03:56.069 --> 03:58.171
won't talk to her mother about
certain marital problems.

04:01.008 --> 04:02.443
You know.

04:02.476 --> 04:03.411
No, I never said that.

04:03.444 --> 04:04.645
You totally know.

04:04.678 --> 04:06.347
What's going on?

04:06.380 --> 04:08.449
Well, there is
really nothing to tell,

04:08.482 --> 04:12.052
because there's nothing to tell.

04:12.085 --> 04:13.754
Nothing?

04:13.787 --> 04:15.623
so?
How much nothing?

04:15.656 --> 04:17.291
Like five weeks of nothing.

04:17.325 --> 04:18.559
And when you're
trying to have a baby,

04:18.592 --> 04:22.062
that is a whole lot of nothing.

04:22.095 --> 04:25.032
So Becky shut Mark down.

04:25.065 --> 04:26.266
I wonder what his
brain's going to do

04:26.300 --> 04:27.134
with all that extra blood?

04:31.972 --> 04:33.641
Yeah, I guess
one could interpret

04:33.674 --> 04:37.378
the situation in that way if
one only had partial knowledge.

04:37.411 --> 04:38.746
Spill it.

04:38.779 --> 04:43.283
Well, according to Becky, she
is not the one holding back.

04:43.317 --> 04:44.818
- Wow, really.
- Yes.

04:44.852 --> 04:47.220
Mark is just not
interested in sex.

04:47.254 --> 04:48.422
Poor Becky

04:48.456 --> 04:51.792
Yeah, now she'll have
to teach him to talk.

04:51.825 --> 04:55.095
Please, don't tell Becky that
I told you, because I promised.

04:55.128 --> 04:56.530
You know I wouldn't do that.

04:56.564 --> 05:00.734
Besides, my word is every
bit as good as yours.

05:00.768 --> 05:02.803
I Think maybe she felt
more comfortable talking

05:02.836 --> 05:07.174
to someone who might
understand her problem.

05:07.207 --> 05:09.477
Oh, no way.

05:09.510 --> 05:12.079
Your kid's seven months old
and you guys aren't doing it?

05:12.112 --> 05:13.447
No, we're doing it.

05:13.481 --> 05:17.217
But things have
gotten kind of rushed.

05:17.250 --> 05:18.686
Well, rushed is kind of fun.

05:18.719 --> 05:19.953
You know, sometimes
me and Dan try

05:19.987 --> 05:21.254
to race the microwave popcorn.

05:29.229 --> 05:32.332
It's not fun to
rush every time.

05:32.366 --> 05:33.967
Fred is so nervous
about waking the baby up

05:34.001 --> 05:37.270
that he is beginning to
gloss over some vital areas.

05:43.310 --> 05:45.646
Oh my God, are
you talking about?

05:45.679 --> 05:50.217
You mean, he gets in the
elevator, but he won't go down.

05:53.387 --> 05:55.322
If I wasn't gay
before, I would be now.

05:59.159 --> 06:00.894
Well, if you weren't
gay before then,

06:00.928 --> 06:03.631
a whole bunch of guys
owe you a big apology.

06:06.199 --> 06:11.171
Hey, have you gotten really
horny part of pregnancy yet?

06:11.204 --> 06:14.074
Well, you don't see
any delivery boys

06:14.107 --> 06:17.210
circling my house yet, do you?

06:17.244 --> 06:19.179
Well, that must
be tough on Dan,

06:19.212 --> 06:20.848
if you're not all
that interested.

06:20.881 --> 06:23.584
Yeah, he's convinced that it's
because we're stale, you know.

06:23.617 --> 06:25.118
So he thinks he's
getting these ideas

06:25.152 --> 06:28.622
out of these crazy men's
magazines, and stuff to try,

06:28.656 --> 06:29.723
you know.

06:29.757 --> 06:36.063
Like last night, he
wanted to suck my toes.

06:36.096 --> 06:37.598
Did he?

06:37.631 --> 06:38.966
Yeah.

06:38.999 --> 06:40.868
Did it get you excited?

06:40.901 --> 06:41.769
No.

06:41.802 --> 06:43.303
But it got him going.

06:43.336 --> 06:44.237
Really?

06:44.271 --> 06:45.138
Dan?

06:45.172 --> 06:46.239
No!

06:46.273 --> 06:47.708
Well, it turned out
pretty good, you know.

06:47.741 --> 06:50.177
But I wasn't going to
kiss him after that.

06:50.210 --> 06:54.515
[music playing]

06:54.548 --> 06:56.917
[phone ringing]

06:56.950 --> 06:59.820
Hello?

06:59.853 --> 07:02.823
Oh, David Healy.

07:02.856 --> 07:04.892
Now how do you girls keep
getting this phone number?

07:04.925 --> 07:09.062
We've had it changed five times.

07:09.096 --> 07:10.430
It's a Betty Fuller.

07:10.464 --> 07:13.366
And she wants you to go
have coffee with her.

07:13.400 --> 07:16.003
I don't drink coffee.

07:16.036 --> 07:18.005
Coffee is just a code, David.

07:18.038 --> 07:19.372
She's just trying
to be lady like.

07:19.406 --> 07:20.941
She can't just come right
out and say, Nail me.

07:25.679 --> 07:27.114
Mrs. Conner, just
tell her I'm not in.

07:29.850 --> 07:30.818
Yeah, Betty.

07:30.851 --> 07:33.721
Hi, I'm sorry, but
David isn't here.

07:33.754 --> 07:36.256
Apparently, he had
an emergency slouch

07:36.289 --> 07:38.859
and moped seminar to attend.

07:38.892 --> 07:42.162
But I'll let him
know you called.

07:42.195 --> 07:44.397
Thanks.
I think.

07:44.431 --> 07:47.067
Why don't you go out with her?

07:47.100 --> 07:48.201
Betty's a nice person.

07:48.235 --> 07:50.303
I just don't think it
would work out with her.

07:50.337 --> 07:52.005
Well, it doesn't have
to work out with her.

07:52.039 --> 07:53.440
She's a practice girl.

07:53.473 --> 07:55.543
You know, she's like the
frame that you ball before you

07:55.576 --> 07:56.644
actually start keeping score.

07:59.813 --> 08:01.749
Look, I'm just not ready
to have coffee with someone.

08:01.782 --> 08:03.183
When I'm ready to have
coffee with someone,

08:03.216 --> 08:05.118
then I'll have
coffee with someone.

08:05.152 --> 08:06.720
Good afternoon, Family.

08:06.754 --> 08:09.289
Pseudo family.

08:09.322 --> 08:10.190
Boy, do I feel good.

08:10.223 --> 08:11.091
Well, of course you do.

08:11.124 --> 08:13.961
You haven't been here all day.

08:13.994 --> 08:15.663
You are looking
at a man whose crew

08:15.696 --> 08:17.297
just finished the
yearly maintenance

08:17.330 --> 08:18.465
on the school buses.

08:18.498 --> 08:19.399
Five, count them.

08:19.432 --> 08:21.034
Five days early.

08:21.068 --> 08:23.537
City's so pleased,
they're talking bonus.

08:23.571 --> 08:26.506
It will never happen,
but there is talk.

08:26.540 --> 08:28.776
Well, um, David, could you
get out of here, because I need

08:28.809 --> 08:31.378
to speak to Mr. Conner alone.

08:31.411 --> 08:32.780
OH, Roseanne,
don't speak to me

08:32.813 --> 08:38.085
alone, not when I just finished
the school bus five days early.

08:38.118 --> 08:40.988
Mr. Conner wants you to stay
and yet, I want you to leave.

08:41.021 --> 08:42.289
Whatever will you do?

08:49.229 --> 08:50.564
What?

08:50.598 --> 08:52.733
OK, Becky and Mark, they're
having all these sex problems.

08:52.766 --> 08:53.934
And I don't know
all the details.

08:53.967 --> 08:56.804
But after you talk to
Mark, then you fill me in.

08:56.837 --> 08:58.438
I just remembered
something that I have

08:58.471 --> 08:59.406
to deal with that isn't this.

08:59.439 --> 09:00.307
No.

09:00.340 --> 09:01.709
Come on.

09:01.742 --> 09:03.811
Now this is serious because this
could split Becky and Mark up.

09:03.844 --> 09:05.012
And you know how
our daughters are.

09:05.045 --> 09:06.013
They dump them.

09:06.046 --> 09:10.350
And then we're
forced to raise them.

09:10.383 --> 09:11.885
Why don't you talk to Becky?

09:11.919 --> 09:13.754
Because Becky isn't
the one having a problem.

09:13.787 --> 09:16.056
Mark's the one
that won't put out.

09:16.089 --> 09:22.329
Oh, boy, am I swamped
with the noises in my head.

09:22.362 --> 09:23.363
Come on, Dan.

09:23.396 --> 09:24.264
This is serious.

09:24.297 --> 09:25.666
He's got to talk to another man.

09:25.699 --> 09:27.334
No way.

09:27.367 --> 09:29.536
Men don't talk to each other
about this kind of stuff.

09:29.569 --> 09:30.704
Well, I thought
you and Mark were

09:30.738 --> 09:31.872
supposed to be good friends.

09:31.905 --> 09:34.341
- We are friends.
- You men.

09:34.374 --> 09:35.976
You say you have these
great friendships.

09:36.009 --> 09:38.411
But all you really have is
just another hairy person

09:38.445 --> 09:42.115
to eat chips and itch with.

09:42.149 --> 09:44.217
What could be better?

09:44.251 --> 09:45.686
You have to do it, Dan.

09:45.719 --> 09:47.020
You have to do it to help Becky.

09:47.054 --> 09:48.822
No.

09:48.856 --> 09:50.724
I helped my daughter
learn to walk.

09:50.758 --> 09:52.993
I helped my daughter
learn how to ride a bike.

09:53.026 --> 09:54.594
I helped my daughter
with her homework.

09:54.628 --> 09:56.664
