And what's worse, we
all know that we know.

15:27.427 --> 15:31.864
Well, it's not easy
being a woman, is it, Dan?

15:31.898 --> 15:33.566
You just don't get it, do you?

15:33.600 --> 15:36.036
It's going to take years of us
guys not talking to each other

15:36.069 --> 15:39.039
to get back to where we were.

15:39.072 --> 15:40.640
Well, why don't you
just cut your tongues out?

15:40.673 --> 15:42.309
We all know that Fred
doesn't need his.

15:48.948 --> 15:51.985
I can play this little
game too, Roseanne.

15:52.019 --> 15:55.855
How would you like it if I told
everyone our personal stuff?

15:55.888 --> 15:57.991
What if I told everybody
that you're not

15:58.025 --> 16:00.393
too interested in sex lately?

16:00.427 --> 16:02.395
Well, yeah, why don't you go
tell everybody that your wife

16:02.429 --> 16:03.563
turns all time for sex.

16:03.596 --> 16:07.734
That would really embarrass me.

16:07.767 --> 16:10.037
This sucks.

16:10.070 --> 16:10.937
Fine, Mark.

16:10.970 --> 16:12.272
Just drive off, you jerk.

16:16.776 --> 16:17.677
I can't believe Aunt Jackie.

16:17.710 --> 16:19.846
I confided a huge secret to her.

16:19.879 --> 16:21.114
And then she went and told Fred.

16:21.148 --> 16:22.949
And now Mark is
madder than ever.

16:22.982 --> 16:23.850
I know.

16:23.883 --> 16:24.684
We all know.

16:26.986 --> 16:28.221
What?

16:28.255 --> 16:30.523
Well, your Aunt Jackie
is a huge blabbermouth

16:30.557 --> 16:32.859
and she tells
everybody everything.

16:32.892 --> 16:34.594
You should hear what she
told about your father.

16:34.627 --> 16:35.428
Roseanne!

16:38.165 --> 16:39.432
This is great.

16:39.466 --> 16:42.902
so everyone knows that my
husband finds me repulsive.

16:42.935 --> 16:45.505
Oh, Becky, nobody thinks that.

16:45.538 --> 16:46.339
Just leave me alone.

16:49.042 --> 16:51.344
Well, I hope you're happy.

16:51.378 --> 16:54.247
You just managed to make
everyone's life worse.

16:54.281 --> 16:57.750
Yes, and I'm exhausted.

16:57.784 --> 17:00.920
I could use a little
help next time.

17:00.953 --> 17:07.327
[music playing]

17:07.360 --> 17:08.328
Hi.

17:08.361 --> 17:09.762
I brought you up some dinner.

17:09.796 --> 17:11.098
Everybody was real
hungry, though,

17:11.131 --> 17:14.033
so it's mostly just peas.

17:14.067 --> 17:15.235
I don't want any.

17:23.276 --> 17:25.845
Becky, remember when
you were a little girl.

17:25.878 --> 17:28.615
And I used to come up here
and sit on the bed with you.

17:28.648 --> 17:30.417
And I used brush your hair.

17:30.450 --> 17:33.286
And you'd tell me about all the
stuff that happened to that day

17:33.320 --> 17:35.322
in school.

17:35.355 --> 17:37.957
We never did that.

17:37.990 --> 17:40.360
Well, I always wanted to.

17:40.393 --> 17:41.328
Mom, I should be studying.

17:45.064 --> 17:46.133
You know, Becky.

17:46.166 --> 17:47.900
This problem that you
and Mark are having.

17:47.934 --> 17:49.469
Mom, I'm really not
comfortable talking

17:49.502 --> 17:50.370
about this with you.

17:50.403 --> 17:51.271
Well, why not?

17:51.304 --> 17:52.739
We're two married, mature women.

17:52.772 --> 17:55.975
And I think that we can
talk about, you know, it.

17:56.008 --> 17:58.211
Mom.

17:58.245 --> 18:00.046
It's one of the great
things about being women,

18:00.079 --> 18:03.616
you know, we can talk intimately
in a way that men can't.

18:03.650 --> 18:04.884
You know, sober.

18:07.520 --> 18:10.957
Mom, I'm pretty sure I
know what Mark's problem is.

18:10.990 --> 18:13.260
He's feeling like I'm moving
away from him, because I'm

18:13.293 --> 18:15.562
going to school and he's not.

18:15.595 --> 18:16.663
Oh, yeah.

18:16.696 --> 18:18.030
Well, that makes sense.

18:18.064 --> 18:19.699
That's really good.

18:19.732 --> 18:21.501
I know this is not
my fault. I mean,

18:21.534 --> 18:22.569
Mark's just feeling insecure.

18:22.602 --> 18:24.070
And he needs to work it out.

18:24.103 --> 18:25.505
Well.
well, that's great.

18:25.538 --> 18:26.739
See?

18:26.773 --> 18:31.244
See, this kind of girl
talk can really help a lot.

18:31.278 --> 18:34.914
Well, I got most
of from David.

18:34.947 --> 18:38.251
You girl talked with David?

18:38.285 --> 18:41.120
Talking to David made
me feel a lot better.

18:41.154 --> 18:44.591
I bet it made you
feel taller too?

18:44.624 --> 18:45.725
You ready to go?

18:45.758 --> 18:47.194
Where are you going?

18:47.227 --> 18:48.127
Just to talk.

18:48.161 --> 18:49.496
David's really sweet.

18:49.529 --> 18:50.563
Well, I'm sweet.

18:50.597 --> 18:53.233
How come nobody
ever talks to me.

18:53.266 --> 18:56.736
We're just going to
go have some coffee.

18:56.769 --> 19:00.373
David is not ready for coffee.

19:00.407 --> 19:02.275
Yeah, I think I am.

19:02.309 --> 19:03.543
Don't you think
you should be having

19:03.576 --> 19:06.112
coffee with your own husband?

19:06.145 --> 19:07.880
Mark doesn't want any.

19:07.914 --> 19:09.782
Hey, if Mark's not
interested in having coffee,

19:09.816 --> 19:11.150
then I'll have coffee with her.

19:15.755 --> 19:23.230
[music playing]

19:23.263 --> 19:26.466
So I had to hear it
again from Dan last night.

19:26.499 --> 19:29.702
I don't cuddle enough.

19:29.736 --> 19:31.070
Oh, man, cuddling?

19:35.107 --> 19:36.376
I hate it.

19:36.409 --> 19:38.578
I work hard all day.

19:38.611 --> 19:39.946
I come home.

19:39.979 --> 19:42.014
I want my dinner.

19:42.048 --> 19:43.716
Little zippety doo da.

19:47.119 --> 19:47.987
Slap him on the ass.

19:48.020 --> 19:48.921
I'm out like a light.

19:55.462 --> 19:58.064
I always take a couple extra
minutes with Dan, you know,

19:58.097 --> 19:59.432
to finish him off.

19:59.466 --> 20:01.834
Otherwise, I have to lay
there and listen to him gripe.

20:05.772 --> 20:07.640
I really feel bad about
what happened in the garage

20:07.674 --> 20:10.610
the other day.

20:10.643 --> 20:11.511
I know.

20:11.544 --> 20:15.014
I really hurt you, Mark.

20:15.047 --> 20:15.982
I wanted to call you.

20:16.015 --> 20:17.450
But I just didn't
feel like I could.

20:20.186 --> 20:21.053
You can call me, Fred.

20:21.087 --> 20:22.088
Anytime, you know that.

20:22.121 --> 20:24.257
Even if it's just the talk.

20:24.291 --> 20:27.694
You see, Mark we don't
always get that from you.

20:27.727 --> 20:30.229
I mean, sometimes you seem so--

20:30.263 --> 20:32.465
Distant.

20:32.499 --> 20:33.333
I know.

20:33.366 --> 20:36.936
And I don't mean to be.

20:36.969 --> 20:38.671
Oh, this is delicious, Dan.

20:44.110 --> 20:44.977
Yeah?

20:45.011 --> 20:47.547
But how many calories?

20:47.580 --> 20:49.115
Oh, like you should worry.

20:53.553 --> 20:56.623
Hey, now, I've got
my problem areas.

20:56.656 --> 20:58.458
Oh, please, I would
trade my waistline

20:58.491 --> 20:59.492
for your thighs any day.

21:03.296 --> 21:05.865
Why don't you roosters
give it a rest, huh?

21:05.898 --> 21:07.734
There'll be plenty to
gossip about tomorrow.

21:10.670 --> 21:11.471
Roseanne, please.

21:15.942 --> 21:18.845
And while we're on the
subject there, cupcake,

21:18.878 --> 21:21.213
I think you could do
without that pudding.

21:29.356 --> 21:31.691
Why must you always embarrass
me in front of my friends?

21:35.094 --> 21:49.976
[music playing]

21:54.881 --> 21:56.349
[tone]
